# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 11 (Enterprise Analytics)

Spec: `docs/13_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_11_ANALYTICS.md`

## Rules

- Emit product/marketing events only via `trackAnalyticsEvent` / `trackConversionEvent` / `trackProductEvent` / `trackAITelemetryEvent`.
- Register sinks with an explicit consent category (`analytics` vs `marketing`).
- Never include secrets, passwords, API keys, prompts, org/user/client IDs in analytics props.
- Prefer `feature`, `module`, `surface`, `result`, `duration_ms`, `funnel_stage` for measurable envelopes.
- Use `trackBillingLifecycleEvent` as the billing integration point — do not couple analytics into Paddle webhook business logic in this chapter.
- Keep providers modular (`providers.ts` / `ANALYTICS_CONFIG`) — no hard-coded third-party business rules.
- Analytics must never change auth, RBAC, RLS, Paddle, API, or application behaviour.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 11 work.
